pm.test("status code validation",function(){
	//2 ways to test pm,
	// 1.
	pm.response.to.have.status("OK");
	// 2.
	pm.expect(pm.response.status).to.equal("OK");

});

HOW TO VALIDATE PAYLOAD?
------------------------
difference between eql and equal
2 objects are there eg: student{}, emp{}
eql-used to validate only- students -objects properties
equal-compares 2 diff objects student vs employee -age check,city check...



-------
pm.test("Successful POST request", function () {
    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201]);
});

pm.test("Validation", () => {
    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.equal(200);
});


2 ways of BDD to fetch values from response

1.  pm.response.to.have.______________-->status/code/json[object.id/object.name/object.price/] (______________)--> 1/tim/1000
2.  pm.response.__________-->[|json-->[obj.name/obj.price]| /status/code/body].to.eql(___________)-->[200/ok/total response]


