//API Chaining
EXAMPLE1:Setting up environment with booking id ,storing and using them in get calls to avoid 404 forbidden ,or 400 bad req

step1://creating a QAenvironment
step2:// to get newly created posting bookingid  from POST REQ 
step3:// and passing them to next get request-ValidatePostingResponseBody
step4://check CHAINING flow ==> from post REQ-get bookingid -pass-to get req-and fetch details-save response json-validate booking details 

scalar variable- {{ }}- env value which stored used inside script
in selenium-scalar var- ${variable}

//put req- to update details with new details

to add put req we need token to update server
//so create token req- then pass token to the post req in headers

EXAMPLE2 of API chaining:
--------------------------

step1:
post(createBookingID)-get(readBookingDetails-should have our booking json body passed)
step2:
Create a token-set token to env variable-then pass token value to Header of PUT req
step3:
create put req-set env of booking ID in URL endpoint on PUT req- then add Header with Env token id 
step4:
Create put req to update booking details created on step1
step5:
goto get req on step 1 used, and send req to see updated json body-body should be updated with new values we used on PUT
step6:
write pm validation to check pm.req.json() contain expected booking id,name,and prices


